land","Besford, Worcestershire, England":"Besford, Worcestershire, England"},"en":{"1146–1176":"1146–1176","1140–1177":"1140–1177","1145–1215":"1145–1215","1146–1200":"1146–1200","1162–1254":"1162–1254","1165–Male":"1165–Deceased","1176–1246":"1176–1246","–Male":"Deceased","1110–1154":"1110–1154","–Female":"Deceased","about 1160":"about 1160","1165":"1165","1176":"1176","1154":"1154","1110":"1110","1175":"1175","1162":"1162","1140":"1140","1215":"1215","1246":"1246","1146":"1146","1200":"1200","1145":"1145","about 1139":"about 1139","1254":"1254","1177":"1177","about 1154":"about 1154","Throckmorton, Worcestershire, England":"Throckmorton, Worcestershire, England","Worcester, Worcestershire, England":"Worcester, Worcestershire, England","Besford, Worcestershire, England":"Besford, Worcestershire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Throckmorton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Throckmorton in Worcestershire, which is named with Old English <i>throc</i> ‘beam bridge’ + <i>mere</i> ‘pool’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’.","History: The Throckmorton family was powerful and influential in England in Tudor times, but has since almost died out there. American bearers of the name trace